data.name: LBL_AboutA2.Text
data.value: The design has been refreshed with a modern look, and the functionality has been expanded. As always, Small-Demo-Manager is open source. The new name is easier to read and avoids potential issues with the CS2 trademark.

data.name: LBL_AboutMe.Text
data.value:
Hi, I’m Pythaeus, and I love developing open-source software. This project, which extracts data from demos and calculates the Bitfield number, was inspired after I watched a video by KEROVSKI.
I’m a strong supporter of the anti-cheat community, and with this tool I want to make their work a little easier.

data.name: LBL_AboutB1.Text
data.value: Special thanks go, as always, to KEROVSKI, who inspired me to create and improve this software. I would also like to thank everyone who puts effort into raising awareness about the cheating problem in CS2, including @KEROVSKI_, @HaiX, @LobaCS2, @neokCS, and many others.

data.name: LBL_GuideSettings.Text
data.value:
In the settings, you can switch to Dark Mode.
You can also adjust the paths: one for your CS2 demo folder (it should look something like ..\Counter-Strike Global Offensive\game\csgo), and another for the folder where extracted audio files will be saved.

data.name: LBL_GuideAudio.Text
data.value: Just like with the previous version, you can extract the in-game voice chat audio from demos recorded on SourceTV servers and copy the individual files to any folder you like. You can even double-click on a file to listen to it directly. Please note that demos from Premier and Competitive modes do not contain voice recordings.
